==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[acceleratus]]'', past participle of ''[[accelerare]]'', formed from ''[[ad-]]'' + ''[[celerare]]'' "to hasten", which from ''[[celer]]'' "quick". See [[celerity]].

===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/əkˈseləˌreɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|accelerat|e||}}
# {{transitive}} To cause to move [[faster]]; to [[quicken]] the motion of; to add to the [[speed]] of.
# {{transitive}} To quicken the natural or ordinary [[progression]] or [[process]] of; as, to '''accelerate''' the growth of a plant, the increase of wealth, etc.
# {{transitive}} To [[hasten]], as the occurence of an event; as, to '''accelerate''' our departure.
# {{intransitive}} To become faster; to begin to move more quickly.

